# Pong RL — Deep Q-Network

A reinforcement learning agent that learns to play single-player Pong
using a **Deep Q-Network (DQN)**.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  │                               │           │
│  │  ←——— ball bounces ————→     │  RIGHT    │
│  │                               │  WALL     │
│  PADDLE                          │           │
│  (AI)                                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Project structure

```
pong_rl/
├── pong_env.py       # Custom environment (ball, paddle, physics)
├── dqn_agent.py      # DQN agent (Q-network + replay buffer)
├── train.py          # Training loop
├── play.py           # Watch a trained agent play
└── requirements.txt
```

---

## Quick start

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

> Needs Python 3.9+. A GPU is optional but speeds things up.

### 2. Train the agent

```bash
python train.py
```

Training runs for **2 000 episodes** by default and prints stats every 20:

```
  Ep   20 | AvgReward   -3.12 | AvgHits   0.2 | ε 0.905 | ⏱    4.1s
  Ep   40 | AvgReward   -1.87 | AvgHits   0.8 | ε 0.818 | ⏱    8.3s
  ...
  Ep 2000 | AvgReward   18.45 | AvgHits  12.3 | ε 0.050 | ⏱  412.0s
```

Checkpoints are saved to:
- `pong_dqn.pth`       — latest
- `pong_dqn_best.pth`  — highest average reward

### 3. Watch the trained agent play

```bash
python play.py
```

A pygame window opens and the agent plays 10 games autonomously.

