## How it works

### Environment (`pong_env.py`)

| Component | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **State** | `[ball_x, ball_y, ball_vx, ball_vy, paddle_y]` — 5 normalised floats |
| **Actions** | 0 = stay, 1 = up, 2 = down |
| **Rewards** | +2 per hit (bonus grows with rally length), +0.05/frame alive, −5 for miss |
| **Episode end** | Ball exits left side of screen |

### Agent (`dqn_agent.py`)

| Hyper-parameter | Value |
|-----------------|-------|
| Architecture | 5 → 128 → 128 → 3 |
| Optimizer | Adam, lr = 1e-3 |
| Discount γ | 0.99 |
| Replay buffer | 50 000 transitions |
| Batch size | 64 |
| ε start → end | 1.0 → 0.05 (decay 0.995/episode) |
| Target-net sync | every 300 steps |
| Loss | Huber (smooth L1) |

### Training flow

```
for each episode:
    reset env → get state s
    loop:
        select action a (ε-greedy)
        execute a → (s', r, done)
        store (s, a, r, s', done) in replay buffer
        sample mini-batch → compute Bellman target → update online net
        every 300 steps → copy online net → target net
    until done
```

